    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-01-26T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-26T01:00:00-05:00" n="104"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/1–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-01-26T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 26, 1949—2 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 27—2:54 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>226. In rejecting Peng Chao-hsien as Nationalist representative to proposed
                    Kmt–CCP peace negotiations and terming him war criminal, North Shensi broadcast
                    January 25 made its first addition to list of 43 war criminals announced
                    Christmas Day.</p>
                <p>Despite numerous current rumors, to our knowledge no names have yet been
                    officially removed from initial war criminal list except possibly that of Fu
                        Tso-yi<note n="64" xml:id="d104fn64">Commander in Chief of Rebellion
                        Suppression Forces in North China.</note> who has “partly atoned for his
                    crimes”. On the contrary, January 25 broadcast reaffirmed intention to expand
                    list.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
